headlines.description: — Boston Celtics center Kristaps Porzingis has a message for teams coming into TD Garden.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jaylen Brown's big 4th quarter carries Celtics to 114-97 win over Magic for 14-0 start at home

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — CJ McCollum scored 29 points, Brandon Ingram added 26 and the New Orleans Pelicans set a franchise record with 22 3-pointers in rolling past Victor Wembanyama and the San Antonio Spurs 146-110 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pelicans set franchise record with 22 3-pointers, roll past Wembanyama, Spurs 146-110

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 26 points and 17 rebounds, passing Kareem Abdul-Jabbar to become the Bucks' career rebounding leader, and Damian Lillard scored 39 points in Milwaukee's 128-119 victory over the Houston Rockets on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo passes Abdul-Jabbar for Bucks' career rebounding record in victory over Rockets

headlines.description: — Devin Booker shook off a subpar shooting night, scoring 11 of his 27 points in the fourth quarter, and the Phoenix Suns overcame a 16-point deficit to beat the Washington Wizards 112-108 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Devin Booker sparks big 4th quarter, Suns rally to beat Wizards 112-108

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry’s NBA-record 3-pointer streak ended at 268 games Sunday night in the Golden State Warriors’ 118-114 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry's 3-pointer streak ends at 268 games in Warriors' win in Portland
